00:11:57.180 --> 00:11:59.700
all organic, no paid UA.

00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:03.240
That's pretty cool, right?

00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:05.850
So as our network in the
industry grew and many of you

00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:09.690
started sharing numbers with
us and we got a little help

00:12:09.690 --> 00:12:11.790
from app [INAUDIBLE]
premium, we realized

00:12:11.790 --> 00:12:17.550
that we had a lot to improve
when it comes to monetization.

00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:19.520
We hired a full-time
analyst, and that

00:12:19.520 --> 00:12:23.570
helped us transitioning from
basing most of our decisions

00:12:23.570 --> 00:12:27.110
on gut feeling to really
diving into the numbers.

00:12:27.110 --> 00:12:29.960
We started doing some UA,
and it became more clear

00:12:29.960 --> 00:12:33.850
that we need a new strategy
to increase our revenue.

00:12:33.850 --> 00:12:35.910
So that's what we've
been doing this year is

00:12:35.910 --> 00:12:38.670
focusing on the numbers,
analyzing everything.

00:12:38.670 --> 00:12:44.170
And our analyst introduced this
term of MMM, Making More Money.

00:12:44.170 --> 00:12:48.380
Maybe you do that
the same as well.

00:12:48.380 --> 00:12:51.030
We have been very
careful, scared

00:12:51.030 --> 00:12:53.590
of harming the user experience.

00:12:53.590 --> 00:12:57.300
So we have been trying to
enhance our monetization,

00:12:57.300 --> 00:12:59.550
and it's been well-received.

00:12:59.550 --> 00:13:00.990
And everybody's happy.

00:13:00.990 --> 00:13:03.760
The analyst is happy,
and we're happy.

00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:06.370
We've been working
more focused with ASO,

00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:08.280
and I brought this example here.

00:13:08.280 --> 00:13:11.370
When we first launched
"Fun Run 3 Arena,"

00:13:11.370 --> 00:13:12.930
we didn't even call
it "Fun Run 3."

00:13:12.930 --> 00:13:15.420
We called it "Fun Run Arena"
because our gut feeling said

00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:17.350
that that was the
right thing to do.

00:13:17.350 --> 00:13:20.580
So this was the icon,
also based on gut feeling.

00:13:20.580 --> 00:13:22.830
A year after launch,
we did an experiment

00:13:22.830 --> 00:13:26.440
in Google Play just
adding the number 3.

00:13:26.440 --> 00:13:29.070
And as you can see the
results, it became clear to us

00:13:29.070 --> 00:13:34.580
that we should update both
the title and the icon.

00:13:34.580 --> 00:13:37.190
So "Fun Run 3" was
clearly our star.

00:13:39.890 --> 00:13:42.340
But what's the challenge?

00:13:42.340 --> 00:13:44.360
The monetization,
when we compared it

00:13:44.360 --> 00:13:48.470
to the older titles, two to
four times better ARPDAU.

00:13:48.470 --> 00:13:50.890
Retention was
clearly a lot better.

00:13:50.890 --> 00:13:53.240
Technology-- we
built the newest game

00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:57.690
in Unity, which made it
easier for us to maintain.

00:13:57.690 --> 00:14:00.480
This is the game where
we had the dedicated team

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:03.510
and want to deliver the
best gameplay and best user

00:14:03.510 --> 00:14:05.120
experience.

00:14:05.120 --> 00:14:07.353
And I know that
Nacho and [INAUDIBLE]

00:14:07.353 --> 00:14:09.020
if you have seen their
talks before, you

00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:10.603
might have heard
them talking about we

00:14:10.603 --> 00:14:12.650
live in a post-launch world.

00:14:12.650 --> 00:14:14.720
And we agree, and we
plan to do LiveOps

00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:16.610
for this game to
improve it, make

00:14:16.610 --> 00:14:19.550
it even better for a long time.

00:14:19.550 --> 00:14:22.150
So the challenges, as
can see from some numbers

00:14:22.150 --> 00:14:26.080
from AppAnnie showing our
most important keyword.

00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:29.292
The users searching for our
game found the old titles,

00:14:29.292 --> 00:14:31.750
and they were a bit confused
it seemed to what to download.

00:14:34.300 --> 00:14:36.520
We even got a big
featuring for "Fun Run 2,"

00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:38.030
and thank you very much.

00:14:38.030 --> 00:14:44.220
We appreciate that, but it
didn't help us grow "Fun Run 3"

00:14:44.220 --> 00:14:45.987
We tried to un-optimize.

00:14:45.987 --> 00:14:47.320
I don't know if you've tried it.

00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:50.310
It can be pretty tricky when
you have millions of downloads

00:14:50.310 --> 00:14:53.740
with a lot of historical data.

00:14:53.740 --> 00:14:59.050
When we launched "Fun Run 1"
and 2, we had organic growth.

00:14:59.050 --> 00:15:01.150
The games went viral,
hit the top charts.

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:03.100
We couldn't do that the same.

00:15:03.100 --> 00:15:05.470
And we were competing not
only with all the games

00:15:05.470 --> 00:15:09.290
in the market but
also ourselves.

00:15:09.290 --> 00:15:13.000
So here, you can
see what happened

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:16.060
when we started testing
removing "Fun Run 1" from Turkey

00:15:16.060 --> 00:15:18.760
where we had a
significant user base.

00:15:18.760 --> 00:15:23.060
People started downloading
"Fun Run 2," not "Fun Run 3."

00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:25.870
So when we removed "Fun
Run 2" from the market,

00:15:25.870 --> 00:15:30.160
finally people were starting to
download "Fun Run 3" as well.

00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:33.370
And it started to grow.

00:15:33.370 --> 00:15:37.890
So we decided to unpublish,
like Nacho talked about.

00:15:37.890 --> 00:15:41.100
We saw from the test that
we expected the new game

00:15:41.100 --> 00:15:44.260
to absorb 90% of the downloads.

00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:47.440
"Fun Run 3" was the game we
wanted our users to download.

00:15:47.440 --> 00:15:49.400
The monetization was better.

00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:51.430
We wanted to be open
with our community

00:15:51.430 --> 00:15:53.040
and inform them
that we were going

00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:54.940
to focus on "Fun Run
3" going forward,

00:15:54.940 --> 00:15:56.365
and we expected a backlash.

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:00.880
We were right.

00:16:00.880 --> 00:16:02.890
"Fun Run 3" absorbed
most of the downloads,

00:16:02.890 --> 00:16:06.460
and it's been growing since.

00:16:06.460 --> 00:16:09.670
So we increased our user
base in "Fun Run 3."

00:16:09.670 --> 00:16:11.890
Overall, we lost
users, but that was

00:16:11.890 --> 00:16:16.570
because we removed older games.

00:16:16.570 --> 00:16:18.730
We managed to
increase our revenue.

00:16:18.730 --> 00:16:21.190
This is from April to August.

00:16:21.190 --> 00:16:22.600
And August and
September has been

00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:24.760
looking pretty nice as well.

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:26.710
We have been able
to free up resources

00:16:26.710 --> 00:16:30.830
to do the great LiveOps we
want to do for "Fun Run 3."

00:16:30.830 --> 00:16:34.010
So our key learnings is
we tested in a market

00:16:34.010 --> 00:16:36.300
where we had a
significant user base.

00:16:36.300 --> 00:16:40.520
We knew what
numbers to look for,

00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:43.350
and we made decisions
based on the key metrics.

00:16:43.350 --> 00:16:45.930
And we were prepared to
let the first game go

00:16:45.930 --> 00:16:49.860
even if there is a lot of
nostalgia there as well.

00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:53.020
We planned for the best and
the worst-case scenario,

00:16:53.020 --> 00:16:57.570
and we had a plan B.
Do not underestimate

00:16:57.570 --> 00:17:00.040
the impact on your community.

00:17:00.040 --> 00:17:03.210
And I brought this example
today because we still

00:17:03.210 --> 00:17:06.270
have a very active
"Fun Run 2" community.

00:17:06.270 --> 00:17:10.349
They even made a petition to
make us bring the game back.

00:17:10.349 --> 00:17:13.079
Every time we post
something in social media,

00:17:13.079 --> 00:17:18.329
like I did today from
here, first reply

00:17:18.329 --> 00:17:20.505
is, please remember "Fun Run 2."

00:17:20.505 --> 00:17:24.690
And they made a very
touching video with music.

00:17:24.690 --> 00:17:27.130
So this happens every time.

00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:29.340
So even though
some of our players

00:17:29.340 --> 00:17:31.830
rated "Fun Run 3" with
one star because they

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:34.680
want us to bring them back, we
have a very active community

00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:38.010
playing "Fun Run 3,"
creating content, and helping

00:17:38.010 --> 00:17:39.640
us grow organically.

00:17:39.640 --> 00:17:43.140
So for us, the right
decision was to divest.

00:17:43.140 --> 00:17:47.100
So I have the honor of
inviting my good friend, Erik,

00:17:47.100 --> 00:17:50.320
to the stage to talk
about their approach,

00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:51.630
which was a bit different.

00:17:51.630 --> 00:17:52.130
Thank you.

00:17:52.130 --> 00:17:54.044
[APPLAUSE]

00:17:54.044 --> 00:17:55.294
ERIK PONTISKOSKI: [INAUDIBLE].

00:17:55.294 --> 00:17:56.502
ANETTE STALOY: There you are.

00:17:56.502 --> 00:17:58.480
ERIK PONTISKOSKI:
Thank you very much.

00:17:58.480 --> 00:18:00.820
Hello, everyone.

00:18:00.820 --> 00:18:05.550
My name is Erik, and
I'm the CEO at Dodreams.

00:18:05.550 --> 00:18:09.000
It's really exciting to be
here in Berlin at Playtime

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.480
and honor to share the stage
with my dear friends, Nacho

00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:15.000
and Anette.

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:19.950
I will present today or talk
about our portfolio strategy.

00:18:19.950 --> 00:18:23.670
I will present what
kind of choices we made,

00:18:23.670 --> 00:18:27.720
explain what was the logic
behind those choices,

00:18:27.720 --> 00:18:32.175
and then present what kind of
impact it had on our business.

00:18:34.925 --> 00:18:39.640
At Dodreams, we make games
where players do stuff

00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:41.300
that dreams are made of.

00:18:41.300 --> 00:18:43.580
So we are Dodreams.

00:18:43.580 --> 00:18:47.800
And we are the makers of
this "Drive Ahead!" portfolio

00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:49.270
of games.

00:18:49.270 --> 00:18:53.000
This key art is for
our game "Drive Ahead!"

00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:55.750
"Drive Ahead!" is a
gladiator car fight game.

00:18:55.750 --> 00:18:57.400
what that means
is you get points

00:18:57.400 --> 00:19:01.190
by hitting your friend
in the head with a car.

00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:03.730
And thank you for that
reaction because that's

00:19:03.730 --> 00:19:08.050
what 100 million people
all around the world

00:19:08.050 --> 00:19:11.500
think also when they decided
to download the game.

00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:14.750
So it's a really fun
and simple premise.

00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:17.080
And in our vision,
"Drive Ahead!" games

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:23.270
are the best way to play, share,
and watch fun gaming content.

00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:26.620
So we have a very large
and active community built

00:19:26.620 --> 00:19:28.330
around video for the game.

00:19:28.330 --> 00:19:30.370
And thanks to this
community, we're

00:19:30.370 --> 00:19:37.310
getting 100,000 new
downloads every single day.

00:19:37.310 --> 00:19:41.200
And this is what the game
originally looked like.

00:19:41.200 --> 00:19:46.100
So it was developed for a sauna
party by one of our employees.

00:19:46.100 --> 00:19:48.260
So he was having some
beers with his friends,

00:19:48.260 --> 00:19:51.007
and they came up
with this idea that,

00:19:51.007 --> 00:19:52.840
hey, what would it look
like if a tank would

00:19:52.840 --> 00:19:55.210
be battling a lorry truck?

00:19:55.210 --> 00:19:57.620
And let's put a
garbage truck there

00:19:57.620 --> 00:20:00.770
against a go-kart or
something like that.

00:20:00.770 --> 00:20:03.490
So even today, the game
looks pretty much the same.

00:20:03.490 --> 00:20:05.290
In the core gameplay,
of course, we've

00:20:05.290 --> 00:20:09.400
brought a lot of
other stuff to it.

00:20:09.400 --> 00:20:12.700
So the first game
went live in 2015.

00:20:12.700 --> 00:20:16.480
And then in 2016, we decided
that, let's have a portfolio

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:17.740
strategy.

00:20:17.740 --> 00:20:21.640
Business logic there is that
we'll do cross promotion,

00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:24.400
we're going to get the higher
number of daily active users,

00:20:24.400 --> 00:20:26.860
and then we're going
to make more money.

00:20:26.860 --> 00:20:31.450
And then also, we had
realized that when

00:20:31.450 --> 00:20:34.990
we made the first game, maybe
we weren't so experienced

00:20:34.990 --> 00:20:36.180
or we made some mistakes.

00:20:36.180 --> 00:20:38.980
So instead of going
through the trouble

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:42.010
of updating the first game,
let's just fix everything

00:20:42.010 --> 00:20:44.680
that we did wrong at one go.

00:20:44.680 --> 00:20:48.560
And we were quite
experimental with it.

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:52.990
So we decided that instead of
just making the second game,

00:20:52.990 --> 00:20:55.070
let's experiment a little bit.

00:20:55.070 --> 00:20:56.560
So we had an idea
for "Drive Ahead!

00:20:56.560 --> 00:21:00.760
Sports," so you can play soccer
and other sports with cars.

00:21:00.760 --> 00:21:04.630
So we made it first an
event in the original game.

00:21:04.630 --> 00:21:07.580
And when we told fans
that summer is over,

00:21:07.580 --> 00:21:09.730
soccer is going away,
then they started

00:21:09.730 --> 00:21:11.782
begging us to bring it back.

00:21:11.782 --> 00:21:13.240
And we said, well,
you can play it.

00:21:13.240 --> 00:21:16.540
But it's going to be
a standalone game.

00:21:16.540 --> 00:21:21.220
And in 2016, actually it
had significant contribution

00:21:21.220 --> 00:21:22.585
to the studio revenue.

00:21:25.210 --> 00:21:31.300
In 2017, we realized that
this portfolio approach

00:21:31.300 --> 00:21:33.610
isn't working perfectly for us.

00:21:33.610 --> 00:21:35.260
So "Drive Ahead!

00:21:35.260 --> 00:21:38.230
Sports" turned out to
be even more a skill

00:21:38.230 --> 00:21:42.730
game than the
original game, so it's

00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:45.190
reaching a more niche audience.

00:21:45.190 --> 00:21:50.020
We were able to be better
in the free-to-play design

00:21:50.020 --> 00:21:50.630
of the game.

00:21:50.630 --> 00:21:54.820
So for example, ARPDAU
was 2.5 times higher.

00:21:54.820 --> 00:21:58.060
But that doesn't really help
when you're reaching only 20%

00:21:58.060 --> 00:22:01.060
of the players from
the original title.

00:22:01.060 --> 00:22:04.450
And the really ugly
thing we did in 2017

00:22:04.450 --> 00:22:06.940
was that we tried
to fix everything

00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:09.880
once again at one go.

00:22:09.880 --> 00:22:12.580
So we made a major
change where changed

00:22:12.580 --> 00:22:16.990
the UI, UX, added a saga
map, and tons of other thing.

00:22:16.990 --> 00:22:18.910
And everybody hated it.

00:22:18.910 --> 00:22:21.580
So we lost half of the
players and revenue,

00:22:21.580 --> 00:22:24.160
and retention was
almost destroyed

00:22:24.160 --> 00:22:26.290
and nearly killed the game.

00:22:26.290 --> 00:22:30.310
And then we also
went all in with AR.

00:22:30.310 --> 00:22:32.110
So we made a game
called "Drive Ahead!

00:22:32.110 --> 00:22:33.250
Minigolf."

00:22:33.250 --> 00:22:35.530
So if we have car
gladiators, this

00:22:35.530 --> 00:22:37.750
is what they do in
their free time.

00:22:37.750 --> 00:22:41.140
And it turned out that we were
there a little bit too early

00:22:41.140 --> 00:22:45.160
and were doing fancy motion
controls with the device.

00:22:45.160 --> 00:22:47.440
People were playing
minigolf like this,

00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:49.940
and it didn't work out either.

00:22:49.940 --> 00:22:55.600
So we discovered that this is
a bit risky as an approach.

00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:59.130
So the decision was that let's
focus on the original title.

00:22:59.130 --> 00:23:03.000
It's getting that 100,000
new players a day.

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:06.420
Good things are that there's
high engagement and virality

00:23:06.420 --> 00:23:08.190
through the community.

00:23:08.190 --> 00:23:13.140
We realized that
we've only scratched

00:23:13.140 --> 00:23:16.810
the surface with
monetization potential there.

00:23:16.810 --> 00:23:20.010
So that's a picture of our team
there with our head of studio

00:23:20.010 --> 00:23:20.980
talking to them.

00:23:20.980 --> 00:23:23.580
And this is the group
that was given the task

00:23:23.580 --> 00:23:26.790
to revamp the game.

00:23:26.790 --> 00:23:29.520
Our approach was the following.

00:23:29.520 --> 00:23:32.370
We realized that it's
too much risk changing

00:23:32.370 --> 00:23:35.620
things in the game, like
making too big changes.

00:23:35.620 --> 00:23:37.860
But we had started
doing LiveOps,

00:23:37.860 --> 00:23:41.400
which is a really great place
to change the rules of the game.

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:45.240
And we see what
works there and then

00:23:45.240 --> 00:23:48.700
bring it into the actual game.

00:23:48.700 --> 00:23:51.480
And so what happened
next was that we

00:23:51.480 --> 00:23:53.260
started doing these iterations.

00:23:53.260 --> 00:23:56.880
So first, we redid the
first-time user experience

00:23:56.880 --> 00:24:01.380
to teach the players how to
watch ads as a daily habit

00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:05.340
and show the value of growing
your collection in the game.

00:24:05.340 --> 00:24:10.050
And then in the second iteration
was our LiveOps events,

00:24:10.050 --> 00:24:13.800
where we gave the
players the feature

00:24:13.800 --> 00:24:17.550
that they could
build a deck of cars

00:24:17.550 --> 00:24:19.470
that they use in a boss fight.

00:24:19.470 --> 00:24:25.670
So both experiments increased
ad engagement rate by 50%,

00:24:25.670 --> 00:24:30.250
and ad engagement is
one of our key KPIs.

00:24:30.250 --> 00:24:32.200
So the lessons we
learned here was

00:24:32.200 --> 00:24:35.800
that when you launch a
new game in a portfolio,

00:24:35.800 --> 00:24:38.140
you have to very
clearly define, what

00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:39.990
is the positioning
of that product,

00:24:39.990 --> 00:24:43.660
and why should it exist
as a standalone game?

00:24:43.660 --> 00:24:46.330
And what has worked
really well for us

00:24:46.330 --> 00:24:49.750
is validating new
features, content, even

00:24:49.750 --> 00:24:53.050
new games with the community.

00:24:53.050 --> 00:24:55.690
We found that when we
openly say that this

00:24:55.690 --> 00:24:57.460
is the good stuff
of our game and this

00:24:57.460 --> 00:24:59.980
is what we're trying
to fix, it actually

00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:02.980
attracts new talent,
then, and ignites

00:25:02.980 --> 00:25:04.660
the passion of the team.

00:25:04.660 --> 00:25:07.420
So we've had really senior
people join the studio

00:25:07.420 --> 00:25:10.660
because they say that the
problems you guys have

00:25:10.660 --> 00:25:12.920
are fun problems to solve.

00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:17.290
So let's fix monetization
when you have a big community.

00:25:17.290 --> 00:25:19.930
And you might wonder what
happened to "Drive Ahead!

00:25:19.930 --> 00:25:20.740
Sports."

00:25:20.740 --> 00:25:23.230
So we still have it live.

00:25:23.230 --> 00:25:26.710
We empowered a fresh,
young, talented team

00:25:26.710 --> 00:25:29.110
to take ownership of the game.

00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:31.000
And they're doing
a really good job

00:25:31.000 --> 00:25:36.180
and really battling against
the "Drive Ahead!" team.

00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:38.590
So that's all for me.

00:25:38.590 --> 00:25:41.760
